## 4. ML Training Pipeline ([train_model.py](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/train_model.py))

This script is run **once before deployment** to produce all artifacts in `models/` and `graphs/`.

### 4.1 Data Loading & Feature Engineering

- Reads [Training.csv](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/data/Training.csv) (4,920 rows, 132 binary symptom columns + `prognosis` label).
- Reads [Symptom-severity.csv](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/data/Symptom-severity.csv) to get per-symptom clinical weights (1–7).
- Creates a **severity-weighted feature matrix**: each binary symptom presence value is multiplied by `weight / max_weight`, so rare but serious symptoms (e.g. `chest_pain` weight = 7) carry more signal than minor ones (e.g. `mild_fever` weight = 1).

### 4.2 Deduplication for Honest Evaluation

The raw dataset has many duplicate rows (only 304 truly unique patterns across 4,920 rows). The pipeline deduplicates before evaluation to prevent inflated metrics. Deployment models are then **re-trained on all 4,920 rows** for maximum coverage.

### 4.3 Models Trained

| Model | Key Hyperparameters |
|---|---|
| Random Forest | 200 trees, `random_state=42` |
| SVM | RBF kernel, C=10, `gamma='scale'`, probability=True |
| Gradient Boosting | 150 estimators, lr=0.1, max_depth=5 |
| Naive Bayes | GaussianNB (default) |
| KNN | k=5, `weights='distance'` |

All models are evaluated with **10-fold Stratified Cross-Validation** on the unique rows. The best model by CV mean is saved as [best_model.pkl](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/models/best_model.pkl).

### 4.4 Ensemble

An **RF(50%) + SVM(35%) + NB(15%) soft-voting ensemble** is saved as [ensemble.pkl](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/models/ensemble.pkl). KNN is excluded because it produces degenerate `predict_proba` outputs. The weighted average of probability vectors across the three models forms the final prediction.

### 4.5 Auxiliary Artifacts Generated

| Artifact | How it's built |
|---|---|
| [cooccurrence.json](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/models/cooccurrence.json) | Symptom co-occurrence matrix (`X_bin.T @ X_bin`), top-6 per symptom |
| [disease_key_symptoms.json](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/models/disease_key_symptoms.json) | Symptoms present in ≥ 50% of training rows per disease |
| [disease_sym_freq.json](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/models/disease_sym_freq.json) | Per-disease symptom frequency (0–1 float) for differential explanation |
| [emergency_combos.json](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/models/emergency_combos.json) | Hard-coded critical symptom combos (heart attack, stroke, meningitis, etc.) |
| [threshold_config.json](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/models/threshold_config.json) | Dynamic confidence thresholds based on severity score bands |
| [body_regions.json](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/models/body_regions.json) | Body region → list of related symptoms (used by body map UI) |

### 4.6 Graphs Generated

| File | Content |
|---|---|
| `disease_distribution.png` | Horizontal bar chart of records per disease in training data |
| `model_comparison.png` | Grouped bar: Test Acc + F1 + CV Acc for all 5 models |
| `cv_boxplot.png` | Box plots of 10-fold CV scores per model |
| `confusion_matrix.png` | Confusion matrix heatmap for the best model (top 15 diseases) |
| `feature_importance.png` | Top 20 symptoms by Random Forest feature importance |
