## 5. Flask Application ([app.py](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/app.py))

The application loads all model artifacts at **startup** and keeps them in memory for fast inference.

### 5.1 Startup Loading

```python
model            = best_model.pkl          # single best model
le               = label_encoder.pkl       # disease name encoder
symptoms_list    = symptoms_list.pkl       # 132 feature names (ordered)
sev_weights      = severity_weights.pkl    # {symptom: weight}
ensemble_bundle  = ensemble.pkl            # {models: {RF, SVM, NB}, weights}
cooc_map         = cooccurrence.json
key_sym_map      = disease_key_symptoms.json
disease_sym_freq = disease_sym_freq.json
emergency_combos = emergency_combos.json
threshold_cfg    = threshold_config.json
body_regions     = body_regions.json
```

Reference CSVs (`description`, `medications`, `precautions`, `diets`, `workouts`) are loaded into pandas DataFrames and converted to plain Python dicts for O(1) lookups.

### 5.2 Core Inference Logic

#### Predict Disease ([predict_disease](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/app.py#168-203))

1. Builds a 132-element float vector. Each selected symptom gets value [(clinical_weight / max_weight) × duration_multiplier](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/app.py#757-761).
2. Runs `predict_proba` on each of the three ensemble models.
3. Computes a weighted average: `0.50 × RF + 0.35 × SVM + 0.15 × NB`.
4. Returns [(top_disease, confidence, top5_dict, individual_model_votes)](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/app.py#757-761).

#### Severity Computation ([compute_severity](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/app.py#156-167))

Sums the per-symptom clinical weights, each optionally scaled by a **duration multiplier**:

| Duration | Multiplier |
|---|---|
| Hours | 0.6 (acute, less significant) |
| Days | 1.0 (standard baseline) |
| Weeks | 1.3 (persisting) |
| Months+ (chronic) | 1.6 (highest clinical weight) |

Maximum possible severity score is 35.

#### Dynamic Threshold ([get_dynamic_threshold](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/app.py#149-155))

| Severity Score | Confidence Threshold | Label |
|---|---|---|
| 0 – 5 | 30% | Low Severity |
| 6 – 12 | 45% | Moderate Severity |
| 13 – 20 | 55% | High Severity |
| 21+ | 101% (always consult) | Critical |

If the ensemble confidence falls below the threshold, a **"Consult Doctor"** flag is raised.

#### Risk Factor Boosts ([apply_risk_boosts](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/app.py#205-235))

After the ensemble prediction, disease probabilities in the top-5 are **post-multiplied** based on user-provided risk factors:

| Risk Factor | Boosted Diseases |
|---|---|
| Diabetic | Diabetes ×1.6, Hypertension ×1.2, Heart attack ×1.2 |
| Smoker | Bronchial Asthma ×1.5, Pneumonia ×1.3, Tuberculosis ×1.3 |
| Hypertensive | Hypertension ×1.5, Heart attack ×1.3 |
| Age < 18 | Chicken pox ×1.4, Malaria ×1.2 |
| Age 51–70 | Arthritis ×1.3, Heart attack ×1.2, Diabetes ×1.1 |
| Age 70+ | Arthritis ×1.5, Heart attack ×1.4, Hypertension ×1.3 |

#### Differential Explanation ([get_differential_explanation](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/app.py#237-283))

For each of the top-5 candidate diseases, user symptoms are classified by how often they appear in that disease's training data:

- **Strong** ≥ 70% frequency
- **Moderate** 30–69%
- **Weak** > 0–29%

It also surfaces up to 3 **typical symptoms the user didn't report** (possible missing evidence).

#### Emergency Detection ([check_emergency](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/app.py#308-315))

Before full inference, the symptom set is checked against [emergency_combos.json](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/models/emergency_combos.json). If a critical combination matches (e.g. `chest_pain + breathlessness + sweating` → cardiac emergency), an emergency alert is immediately injected into the response.

#### Smart Suggestions ([get_suggestions](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/app.py#316-325))

Uses the [cooccurrence.json](file:///c:/Users/hp/Documents/main%20projects/CareSense/models/cooccurrence.json) map to find symptoms that most commonly co-occur with the already-selected symptoms, filtered to exclude already-selected ones. Up to 6 suggestions are returned.

### 5.3 API Routes

| Route | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `/` | GET | Main symptom selection page |
| `/predict` | POST (JSON) | Core prediction endpoint — returns full diagnosis JSON |
| `/followup` | POST (JSON) | Re-predicts after user confirms additional suggested symptoms |
| `/rediagnose` | POST (JSON) | Merges previous + new symptoms and re-runs the full pipeline |
| `/autocomplete` | GET (`?q=`) | Returns up to 15 matching symptom names for search |
| `/body_regions` | GET | Returns body region → symptom map for interactive body UI |
| `/suggestions` | POST (JSON) | Returns co-occurrence-based symptom suggestions |
| `/result` | POST (form) | Renders the full result page from a JSON payload |
| `/download_pdf` | POST (JSON) | Generates and streams a PDF report |
| `/analytics` | GET | Renders model performance graphs page |
| `/awareness` | GET | Renders health awareness article page |
| `/diseases` | GET | Renders the disease + symptom encyclopedia page |
| `/graphs/<filename>` | GET | Serves individual graph PNGs |

### 5.4 Prediction JSON Response Structure

A successful `/predict` call returns:
```json
{
  "disease":           "Diabetes",
  "confidence":        87.34,
  "top5":              {"Diabetes": 87.34, "Hypoglycemia": 5.12, ...},
  "differential":      {<disease>: {strong, moderate, weak, missing, match_pct}},
  "model_votes":       {"Random Forest": {disease, confidence}, "SVM": ..., "Naive Bayes": ...},
  "severity_score":    14,
  "severity_label":    "High Severity",
  "threshold_used":    55.0,
  "consult_doctor":    false,
  "emergency":         false,
  "sym_count":         5,
  "suggestions":       ["polyuria", "fatigue", ...],
  "followup_qs":       ["weight_loss", ...],
  "info":              {description, medications, precautions, diets, workouts},
  "selected_symptoms": [...],
  "duration_weights":  {symptom: "days"|"weeks"|"hours"|"chronic"},
  "risk_factors":      {diabetic, smoker, hypertensive, age_group}
}
```

